title: Chase for the Sprint Cup standings entering Talladega
text:
Chase for the Sprint Cup standings entering Talladega Sporting News 1 day ago Jason Boyd
© Provided by Sporting News Joey Logano just made everyone else still in the hunt for a Chase title a bit more nervous.
His second straight victory, this time in the Hollywood Casino 400 at Kansas, means next Sunday at Talladega in the CampingWorld.com 500 (2:30 p.m. on NBC) it will be a free-for-all for the final seven spots in the Eliminator Round of the Chase. Talladega is already one of the wildest, if not the wildest, tracks to run at Sprint Cup race. Now we have this scenario to consider.
MORE: Logano wins, Kenseth sent spinning | Kyle Busch not a fan Think of the the Tazmanian Devil after a couple of Red Bulls. It'll be that fast and that wild and crazy.
Logano also won last week in the Bank of America 500 at Charlotte Motor Speedway. That win already put him into the Eliminator Round of the Chase. Eleven other drivers will now try to grab one of the seven remaining spots in the Eliminator Round.
The winners of next Sunday's CampingWorld.com 500 (500,1 miles, 188 laps) will automatically qualify while the top six drivers in points who have not won one of the three Challenger Round races will advance.
PHOTOS: 2015 Sprint Cup winners | Gordon's final season | Stockcar Toons
